msgstr ""

#. Description of the plugin
#: saddle.php
msgid "Self-hosted MCP server for WordPress. Tiered, default-safe, approval-gated access to posts, pages, and media for AI agents — with no third-party credential custody."
msgstr ""

#. Author of the plugin
#: saddle.php
msgid "PlugPress"
msgstr ""

#. Author URI of the plugin
#: saddle.php
msgid "https://plugpress.co"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:35
msgid "List block types"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:36
msgid "Returns the catalog of editor block types registered on this site, each with its title, category, one-line purpose, and how it is authored: \"content\" (Saddle composes valid markup from your content/attrs), \"attrs-only\" (dynamic block, attributes only), or \"raw-html\" (you must supply exact markup — prefer the other kinds). Read-only. Supports search and category filters. Build pages from real blocks — never approximate a layout by dumping everything into one core/html block."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:44
msgid "Optional keyword filter on name/title/purpose."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:48
msgid "Optional block category filter, e.g. \"text\", \"media\", \"design\"."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:61
msgid "Get block schema"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:62
msgid "Returns one block type's schema: its attributes (with defaults, enums, and which are markup-sourced), placement constraints (required parents/ancestors, allowed children), supports, whether it renders dynamically, and exactly how to author it — with a concrete example node for the common core blocks. Read this before composing a block you have not used yet."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:70
msgid "The block type, e.g. \"core/heading\"."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:83
msgid "Get design tokens"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:84
msgid "Returns this site's design system from theme.json: the color palette, gradients, font sizes, font families, spacing scale, and layout widths, each as {slug, name, value} presets (theme-origin entries are the site's actual brand). Read-only. Use these preset slugs in block attrs (backgroundColor/textColor/fontSize) instead of hardcoded values, so everything you build inherits the site's look and follows future redesigns."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:100
msgid "Bootstrap a design system"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:101
msgid "Seeds a coherent starter design system on a site that has none — a neutral palette with one accent, a type scale, and an 8px spacing scale — so an agent has real tokens to build against instead of inventing values. Admin-tier and confirmation-gated: it returns a preview of exactly what it will write, and only applies on a second call with the confirm_token. Refuses (unless \"force\" is true) when the site already has a substantial design system. On Divi it writes Divi Global Data; on a block theme, set tokens in the Site Editor (not yet automated)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:109
msgid "Optional accent color as a hex value (e.g. \"#2563eb\"). Defaults to a neutral blue."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:113
msgid "Seed even if the site already has a design system. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:117
msgid "The token from the preview response; pass it to apply."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:130
msgid "List section recipes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:131
msgid "Lists Saddle's built-in section recipes — ready-to-insert blueprints for common page sections (hero, features, pricing, testimonials, call-to-action, FAQ) — as {name, title, description}. Read-only. Get one with get-section-recipe, then insert it and swap in real copy and design tokens. Building from a recipe beats composing a section from scratch."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:147
msgid "Get a section recipe"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:148
msgid "Returns one section recipe as a ready-to-insert node tree in Saddle's authoring format ({type, content, attrs, children}), matched to the site's builder — core blocks on a block theme, the builder's modules when a page builder is active. Read-only. Pass it (with real copy substituted) to set-blocks / add-block, or to the builder's set-page. After inserting, apply colors and sizes from get-design-system."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:156
msgid "Recipe name from list-section-recipes (e.g. \"hero\", \"features\", \"pricing\", \"testimonials\", \"cta\", \"faq\")."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:169
msgid "Get design system"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:170
msgid "Returns this site's design system in ONE builder-agnostic shape — colors, fonts, font sizes, spacing, layout widths, plus builder-native design variables and module presets when a page builder is active. On a block theme it reads theme.json; on Divi (with Saddle Pro) it reads Divi's Global Data. Read this FIRST when designing a page, and use the returned slugs/ids instead of hardcoded values so everything you build inherits the real brand. Read-only."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:186
msgid "List block patterns"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:187
msgid "Lists the block patterns registered on this site — prebuilt, theme-styled sections (heroes, feature grids, CTAs, footers) — as summaries: name, title, description, categories. Read-only. Prefer inserting a pattern (saddle/insert-block-pattern) over hand-composing a common section: patterns already match the site's design."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:195
msgid "Optional keyword filter on name/title/description."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:214
msgid "Get page blocks"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:215
msgid "Returns a post or page's block tree as a flat, addressable node list: each node has an address (dot-separated child indexes like \"0.1.0\"), its block type, attributes, child count, and a text excerpt. Addresses are positional — re-read after any edit before addressing further nodes. Read-only. Refuses page-builder-built posts (those are edited with builder tools, not native block tools); classic (non-block) content comes back as one freeform node."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:223
msgid "The post or page ID whose blocks to read."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:236
msgid "Build page blocks"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:237
msgid "Replaces a post or page's entire content with a new block tree — the bulk-build tool for \"design this page\". Each node is {\"type\",\"content\",\"attrs\",\"children\"}: \"content\" carries the text/media payload and Saddle composes editor-valid markup (see saddle/get-block-schema per type); \"attrs\" are block attributes — use preset slugs from saddle/get-design-tokens for colors and sizes. The tree is validated against each block's placement rules and rejected with per-node errors if invalid — nothing partial is saved. If the response carries \"warnings\", those attributes will silently not render (unknown attribute, preset slug, or style group) — fix and re-edit. The previous content is kept as a WordPress revision. Refuses page-builder-built posts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:245
msgid "The post or page whose content to build."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:249
msgid "Top-level blocks (each {\"type\",\"content\",\"attrs\",\"children\"})."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:266
msgid "Add block"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:267
msgid "Inserts one block (with optional children) into a post or page at an addressed position. parent_address is a container node from saddle/get-blocks (\"\" for the top level); position is the index among its children (omit to append). The node uses the same {\"type\",\"content\",\"attrs\",\"children\"} format as saddle/set-blocks. Placement is validated — an insertion that breaks a block's parent/child rules is rejected and nothing is saved. Re-read the page afterwards: addresses shift."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:276
msgid "Container address from saddle/get-blocks; \"\" for the top level."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:280
#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:399
msgid "Index among the parent's children; omit or -1 to append."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:297
msgid "Edit block"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:298
msgid "Rewrites one addressed block on a post or page. Provide \"content\" and/or \"attrs\" — the block is recomposed from its existing values with yours applied (same authoring semantics as saddle/set-blocks), children are kept untouched. The result is validated before saving, and the previous state is kept as a revision. Response \"warnings\" flag attributes that will silently not render."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:307
msgid "Node address from saddle/get-blocks, e.g. \"2.0\"."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:311
msgid "New content payload for the block (string, or the object/array forms its schema documents)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:316
msgid "Attributes merged over the block's existing ones."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:329
msgid "Move block"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:330
msgid "Moves an addressed block (with its subtree) to a new parent and position on the same post or page. Both addresses come from the same saddle/get-blocks read. Moving a block into its own subtree is refused; the result is validated before saving. Re-read the page afterwards: addresses shift."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:340
msgid "Destination container; \"\" for the top level."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:344
msgid "Index among the destination's children; omit or -1 to append."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:357
msgid "Remove block"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:358
msgid "Removes an addressed block from a post or page. Removing a childless block happens immediately (recoverable from revisions). Removing a container WITH children previews first: the call returns a summary and a confirm_token — repeat the call with that token to execute. Re-read the page afterwards: addresses shift."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:368
msgid "Token from the preview step, required to remove a block that has children."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:381
msgid "Insert block pattern"
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:382
msgid "Inserts a registered block pattern (see saddle/list-block-patterns) into a post or page at an addressed position — the fastest way to add a professional, theme-styled section. parent_address is a container from saddle/get-blocks (\"\" for the top level). The resulting tree is validated before saving; the previous content is kept as a revision. Re-read the page afterwards: addresses shift."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:391
msgid "The pattern name from saddle/list-block-patterns."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:395
msgid "Container address; \"\" for the top level."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:433
msgid "Compose real blocks (\"content\" ones are easiest — saddle/get-block-schema shows each type's exact syntax). Prefer saddle/insert-block-pattern for common sections, and preset slugs from saddle/get-design-tokens for colors and sizes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:447
msgid "Provide a block \"type\", e.g. \"core/heading\"."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:486
msgid "Get one with get-section-recipe, substitute real copy, insert with set-blocks/add-block (or the builder's set-page), then apply colors and sizes from get-design-system."
msgstr ""

#. translators: %s: comma-separated recipe names.
#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:504
#, php-format
msgid "Unknown recipe. Available: %s."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:534
msgid "Insert these nodes (with real copy) via set-blocks/add-block on a block theme, or the builder's set-page/add-module. The recipe is intentionally token-free — apply colors and sizes from get-design-system after inserting."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:554
msgid "This site already has a design system (read it with get-design-system). Pass \"force\": true to seed a starter set anyway."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:608
msgid "Seed a starter design system: 6 brand colors (one accent), a 6-step type scale, and a 7-step 8px spacing scale. Existing tokens are not removed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:632
msgid "No page builder handled the seed. On a block theme, add these colors and sizes in Appearance → Editor → Styles; automated block-theme seeding is not available yet."
msgstr ""

#: includes/abilities/blocks.php:649
msgid "Insert with saddle/insert-block-pattern. Patterns arrive already styled for this theme — prefer them over hand-composing common sections."
msgstr ""

